gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T5 — Login screen Face ID retry (biometry users only)
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S88

context: |
  Applies only when local_use_biometry is true (not trust-device mode).
  After biometry cancel (T2) or when vault has credentials, login screen
  should offer one-tap Face ID retry instead of only username/password.

steps:
  1. In LoginScreen, show quick unlock when: isTauri + local_use_biometry +
     readBiometryUsernameHint + !isBiometryBOPENUntilManualLogin.
  2. Primary button "Unlock with Face ID" above credential form.
  3. Tap → requestBiometricUnlock → handleBiometricRelogin / hydrate path.
  4. Secondary link "Sign in with password" expands credential form.
  5. Pre-fill username from hint; hide password until expanded.
  6. If local_trust_device → do not show this UI (user goes direct per T3).

out:
  - src/screens/login/LoginScreen.tsx
  - src/screens/login/hooks/useLoginFlow.ts
  - locale JSON

done:
  - Biometry user after Face ID cancel → one tap to retry, no password.
  - Trust-device users never land on this flow on normal cold start.
  - OTP/2FA flow unchanged when API returns otp/mail.
